  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I stop my Jamster subscription from charging me money?",
  "response": "To stop your Jamster subscription from charging you money, follow these steps:\n\n1. **Cancel the Subscription:**\n   - **Online:** Log in to your Jamster account on their website. Navigate to the \"My Account\" or \"Subscription\" section, where you should find an option to cancel your subscription. Follow the prompts to complete the cancellation.\n   - **Via Customer Support:** If you can't cancel online, contact Jamster's customer support. You can usually find their contact information on their website. Explain that you want to cancel your subscription and stop future charges.\n\n2. **Confirm Cancellation:** After you've initiated the cancellation, make sure to get a confirmation. This could be an email or a reference number from customer support. Keep this as proof of cancellation.\n\n3. **Check Your Bank or Credit Card Statement:** Monitor your bank or credit card statements to ensure no further charges are made after your cancellation date. If you see any unauthorized charges, contact your bank or credit card company immediately to dispute them.\n\n4. **Unsubscribe from Marketing Emails:** To avoid receiving promotional emails from Jamster, unsubscribe from their mailing list. You can usually do this by clicking the \"unsubscribe\" link at the bottom of their emails.\n\n5. **Remove Payment Information:** If possible, remove your payment information from your Jamster account to prevent any accidental future charges.\n\nIf you encounter any issues during this process, don't hesitate to reach out to Jamster's customer support for assistance.",
